  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the present prospective study is to investigate whether the consumption of certain
      probiotic strains over a six-month winter/spring season would be able to affect the incidence
      and duration of upper respiratory tract infections, in otherwise healthy children as well as
      determining whether a combination of two strains would perform differently from a single
      strain version.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
